### Variables — change port if needed
@base = http://localhost:7071/api

### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 1. Check subscription status
### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
GET {{base}}/EmailWatch/status

### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 2. Register / renew Graph subscription
###    Run this first — Graph will start pushing email notifications
### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
POST {{base}}/EmailWatch/subscribe

### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 3. Delete the active Graph subscription
### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
DELETE {{base}}/EmailWatch/subscribe

### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 4. Simulate a Graph webhook notification
###    Replace AAMkAG... with a real message ID from the mailbox
###    (copy from IncomingEmails table or Graph Explorer)
### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
POST {{base}}/EmailWatch/notify
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "value": [
    {
      "changeType": "created",
      "clientState": "AwningsEmailWatcher-SuperSecretToken",
      "subscriptionId": "local-test",
      "resource": "Users/hello@awningsofireland.com/messages/AAMkAGYOUR_MESSAGE_ID_HERE"
    }
  ]
}

### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 5. Re-process a specific email already in the database
###    Useful when ProcessingStatus = Failed and you want to retry
###    POST a message ID directly to the queue instead of the HTTP trigger
###    (use Azure Storage Explorer → Azurite → email-processing queue → Add message)
### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
